{"questionId":"87a75825-ef1b-4b13-8fde-816390546062_13","correctAnswer":"26/3,8.666,8.667","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Solve the equation","content":"Isolate: $-8|3x-13|+4=-36$ gives $|3x-13|=5$. So $3x-13=5$ or $3x-13=-5$, giving $x=6$ or $x=8/3$."},{"title":"Sum the solutions","content":"Add: $6+\\dfrac{8}{3}=\\dfrac{18}{3}+\\dfrac{8}{3}=\\dfrac{26}{3}$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>26/3</strong>."}]}